  "bio": [
    "Nihat Ozdemir and his billionaire partner, Sezai Bacaksiz, met as students at Gazi University and founded Limak Construction in 1976.",
    "Besides being contractor for some of Turkey's largest infrastructure projects, Limak has operations in energy, tourism, transportation and cement.",
    "It is part of a consortium building Istanbul's third airport. Its largest project outside of Turkey is the Kuwait International Airport.",
    "Limak is a major builder and operator of hydroelectric power plants, ranking among Turkey's top three electricity producers.",
    "Besides Turkey, Limak operates in Kuwait, Egypt, Kosovo, Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus, Eastern Europe, Africa, Pakistan, Ukraine and Russia."
  ],
  "about": [
    "As an academic at what is now Gazi University, Ozdemir was for a short while the assistant of Prof. Necmettin Erbakan, the former prime minister of Turkey."
  ]
